TITLE: Defining Tavily Search Function with TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines an asynchronous TypeScript function `tavilySearch` that takes a query string as input and returns a promise resolving to an object containing the search answer, the original query, and an array of search results. The results array includes the title, URL, content, and score of each search result.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/genaiscript/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/guides/using-secrets.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export async function tavilySearch(query: string): Promise<{ 
    answer: string
    query: string
    results: {
        title: string
        url: string
        content: string
        score: number
    }[]
}> { ... }
```

