TITLE: Workflow State Management with Checkpointer in Typescript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates state management in a GenAIscript workflow using a `checkpointer`. The `entrypoint` is defined with a checkpointer and a function that accesses the previous state using `getPreviousState`. The example shows how the state persists between invocations using the same thread ID.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/genaiscript/blob/main/packages/sample/genaisrc/langgraph.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const myWorkflow = entrypoint(
  { checkpointer, name: "myWorkflow" },
  async (number: number) => {
    const previous = getPreviousState<number>();
    return number + (previous ?? 0);
  }
);

const config = {
  configurable: {
    thread_id: "some_thread_id",
  },
};

await myWorkflow.invoke(1, config); // 1 (previous was undefined)
await myWorkflow.invoke(2, config); // 3 (previous was 1 from the previous invocation)
```

