TITLE: Incorrect Side Effect Handling in Functional API (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates incorrect handling of side effects in the Functional API. Directly including side effects (e.g., writing to a file) in the workflow leads to their re-execution upon workflow resumption, which is generally undesirable. The `fs.writeFile` call will be executed a second time when the workflow resumes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/genaiscript/blob/main/packages/sample/genaisrc/langgraph.md#_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const myWorkflow = entrypoint(
  { checkpointer, name: "myWorkflow" },
  async (inputs: Record<string, any>) => {
    // This code will be executed a second time when resuming the workflow.
    // Which is likely not what you want.
    // highlight-next-line
    await fs.writeFile("output.txt", "Side effect executed");
    const value = interrupt("question");
    return value;
  }
);
```

